58static const AtomString& resourceType()
59{
60 ASSERT(WTF::RunLoop::isMain());
61 static NeverDestroyed<const AtomString> resource("Resource", AtomString::ConstructFromLiteral);
62 return resource;
63}
64
65static size_t computeCapacity(CacheModel cacheModel, const String& cachePath)
66{
67 unsigned urlCacheMemoryCapacity = 0;
68 uint64_t urlCacheDiskCapacity = 0;
69 if (auto diskFreeSize = FileSystem::volumeFreeSpace(cachePath)) {
70 // As a fudge factor, use 1000 instead of 1024, in case the reported byte
71 // count doesn't align exactly to a megabyte boundary.
72 *diskFreeSize /= KB * 1000;
73 calculateURLCacheSizes(cacheModel, *diskFreeSize, urlCacheMemoryCapacity, urlCacheDiskCapacity);
74 }
75 return urlCacheDiskCapacity;
76}
77
78RefPtr<Cache> Cache::open(NetworkProcess& networkProcess, const String& cachePath, OptionSet<CacheOption> options, PAL::SessionID sessionID)
79{
80 if (!FileSystem::makeAllDirectories(cachePath))
81 return nullptr;
82
83 auto capacity = computeCapacity(networkProcess.cacheModel(), cachePath);
84 auto storage = Storage::open(cachePath, options.contains(CacheOption::TestingMode) ? Storage::Mode::AvoidRandomness : Storage::Mode::Normal, capacity);
85
86 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) opened cache storage, success %d", !!storage);
87
88 if (!storage)
89 return nullptr;
90
91 return adoptRef(*new Cache(networkProcess, cachePath, storage.releaseNonNull(), options, sessionID));
92}

97 cache->dumpContentsToFile();

101Cache::Cache(NetworkProcess& networkProcess, const String& storageDirectory, Ref<Storage>&& storage, OptionSet<CacheOption> options, PAL::SessionID sessionID)
102 : m_storage(WTFMove(storage))
103 , m_networkProcess(networkProcess)
104 , m_sessionID(sessionID)
105 , m_storageDirectory(storageDirectory)
106{
107#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_SPECULATIVE_REVALIDATION)
108 if (options.contains(CacheOption::SpeculativeRevalidation)) {
109 m_lowPowerModeNotifier = makeUnique<WebCore::LowPowerModeNotifier>([this](bool isLowPowerModeEnabled) {
110 ASSERT(WTF::RunLoop::isMain());
111 if (isLowPowerModeEnabled)
112 m_speculativeLoadManager = nullptr;
113 else {
114 ASSERT(!m_speculativeLoadManager);
115 m_speculativeLoadManager = makeUnique<SpeculativeLoadManager>(*this, m_storage.get());
116 }
117 });
118 if (!m_lowPowerModeNotifier->isLowPowerModeEnabled())
119 m_speculativeLoadManager = makeUnique<SpeculativeLoadManager>(*this, m_storage.get());
120 }
121#endif
122
123 if (options.contains(CacheOption::RegisterNotify)) {
124#if PLATFORM(COCOA)
125 // Triggers with "notifyutil -p com.apple.WebKit.Cache.dump".
126 int token;
127 notify_register_dispatch("com.apple.WebKit.Cache.dump", &token, dispatch_get_main_queue(), ^(int) {
128 dumpContentsToFile();
129 });
130#endif
131#if PLATFORM(GTK) || PLATFORM(WPE)
132 // Triggers with "touch $cachePath/dump".
133 CString dumpFilePath = fileSystemRepresentation(pathByAppendingComponent(m_storage->basePathIsolatedCopy(), "dump"));
134 GRefPtr<GFile> dumpFile = adoptGRef(g_file_new_for_path(dumpFilePath.data()));
135 GFileMonitor* monitor = g_file_monitor_file(dumpFile.get(), G_FILE_MONITOR_NONE, nullptr, nullptr);
136 g_signal_connect_swapped(monitor, "changed", G_CALLBACK(dumpFileChanged), this);
137#endif
138 }
139}

156Key Cache::makeCacheKey(const WebCore::ResourceRequest& request)
157{
158 // FIXME: This implements minimal Range header disk cache support. We don't parse
159 // ranges so only the same exact range request will be served from the cache.
160 String range = request.httpHeaderField(WebCore::HTTPHeaderName::Range);
161 return { request.cachePartition(), resourceType(), range, request.url().string(), m_storage->salt() };
162}
163
164static bool cachePolicyAllowsExpired(WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy policy)
165{
166 switch (policy) {
167 case WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReturnCacheDataElseLoad:
168 case WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReturnCacheDataDontLoad:
169 return true;
170 case WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::UseProtocolCachePolicy:
171 case WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData:
172 case WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::RefreshAnyCacheData:
173 return false;
174 case WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::DoNotUseAnyCache:
175 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
176 return false;
177 }
178 return false;
179}
180
181static UseDecision responseNeedsRevalidation(NetworkSession& networkSession, const WebCore::ResourceResponse& response, WallTime timestamp, std::optional<Seconds> maxStale)
182{
183 if (response.cacheControlContainsNoCache())
184 return UseDecision::Validate;
185
186 auto age = WebCore::computeCurrentAge(response, timestamp);
187 auto lifetime = WebCore::computeFreshnessLifetimeForHTTPFamily(response, timestamp);
188
189 auto maximumStaleness = maxStale ? maxStale.value() : 0_ms;
190 bool hasExpired = age - lifetime > maximumStaleness;
191#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_STALE_WHILE_REVALIDATE)
192 if (hasExpired && !maxStale && networkSession.isStaleWhileRevalidateEnabled()) {
193 auto responseMaxStaleness = response.cacheControlStaleWhileRevalidate();
194 maximumStaleness += responseMaxStaleness ? responseMaxStaleness.value() : 0_ms;
195 bool inResponseStaleness = age - lifetime < maximumStaleness;
196 if (inResponseStaleness)
197 return UseDecision::AsyncRevalidate;
198 }
199#endif
200
201 if (hasExpired) {
202#ifndef LOG_DISABLED
203 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) needsRevalidation hasExpired age=%f lifetime=%f max-staleness=%f", age, lifetime, maximumStaleness);
204#endif
205 return UseDecision::Validate;
206 }
207
208 return UseDecision::Use;
209}
210
211static UseDecision responseNeedsRevalidation(NetworkSession& networkSession, const WebCore::ResourceResponse& response, const WebCore::ResourceRequest& request, WallTime timestamp)
212{
213 auto requestDirectives = WebCore::parseCacheControlDirectives(request.httpHeaderFields());
214 if (requestDirectives.noCache)
215 return UseDecision::Validate;
216 // For requests we ignore max-age values other than zero.
217 if (requestDirectives.maxAge && requestDirectives.maxAge.value() == 0_ms)
218 return UseDecision::Validate;
219
220 return responseNeedsRevalidation(networkSession, response, timestamp, requestDirectives.maxStale);
221}
222
223static UseDecision makeUseDecision(NetworkProcess& networkProcess, PAL::SessionID sessionID, const Entry& entry, const WebCore::ResourceRequest& request)
224{
225 // The request is conditional so we force revalidation from the network. We merely check the disk cache
226 // so we can update the cache entry.
227 if (request.isConditional() && !entry.redirectRequest())
228 return UseDecision::Validate;
229
230 if (!WebCore::verifyVaryingRequestHeaders(networkProcess.storageSession(sessionID), entry.varyingRequestHeaders(), request))
231 return UseDecision::NoDueToVaryingHeaderMismatch;
232
233 // We never revalidate in the case of a history navigation.
234 if (cachePolicyAllowsExpired(request.cachePolicy()))
235 return UseDecision::Use;
236
237 auto decision = responseNeedsRevalidation(*networkProcess.networkSession(sessionID), entry.response(), request, entry.timeStamp());
238 if (decision != UseDecision::Validate)
239 return decision;
240
241 if (!entry.response().hasCacheValidatorFields())
242 return UseDecision::NoDueToMissingValidatorFields;
243
244 return entry.redirectRequest() ? UseDecision::NoDueToExpiredRedirect : UseDecision::Validate;
245}
246
247static RetrieveDecision makeRetrieveDecision(const WebCore::ResourceRequest& request)
248{
249 ASSERT(request.cachePolicy() != WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::DoNotUseAnyCache);
250
251 // FIXME: Support HEAD requests.
252 if (request.httpMethod() != "GET")
253 return RetrieveDecision::NoDueToHTTPMethod;
254 if (request.cachePolicy() == WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData && !request.isConditional())
255 return RetrieveDecision::NoDueToReloadIgnoringCache;
256
257 return RetrieveDecision::Yes;
258}
259
260static bool isMediaMIMEType(const String& type)
261{
262 return startsWithLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "video/") || startsWithLettersIgnoringASCIICase(type, "audio/");
263}
264
265static StoreDecision makeStoreDecision(const WebCore::ResourceRequest& originalRequest, const WebCore::ResourceResponse& response, size_t bodySize)
266{
267 if (!originalRequest.url().protocolIsInHTTPFamily() || !response.isInHTTPFamily())
268 return StoreDecision::NoDueToProtocol;
269
270 if (originalRequest.httpMethod() != "GET")
271 return StoreDecision::NoDueToHTTPMethod;
272
273 auto requestDirectives = WebCore::parseCacheControlDirectives(originalRequest.httpHeaderFields());
274 if (requestDirectives.noStore)
275 return StoreDecision::NoDueToNoStoreRequest;
276
277 if (response.cacheControlContainsNoStore())
278 return StoreDecision::NoDueToNoStoreResponse;
279
280 if (!WebCore::isStatusCodeCacheableByDefault(response.httpStatusCode())) {
281 // http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7234#section-4.3.2
282 bool hasExpirationHeaders = response.expires() || response.cacheControlMaxAge();
283 bool expirationHeadersAllowCaching = WebCore::isStatusCodePotentiallyCacheable(response.httpStatusCode()) && hasExpirationHeaders;
284 if (!expirationHeadersAllowCaching)
285 return StoreDecision::NoDueToHTTPStatusCode;
286 }
287
288 bool isMainResource = originalRequest.requester() == WebCore::ResourceRequest::Requester::Main;
289 bool storeUnconditionallyForHistoryNavigation = isMainResource || originalRequest.priority() == WebCore::ResourceLoadPriority::VeryHigh;
290 if (!storeUnconditionallyForHistoryNavigation) {
291 auto now = WallTime::now();
292 Seconds allowedStale { 0_ms };
293#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_STALE_WHILE_REVALIDATE)
294 if (auto value = response.cacheControlStaleWhileRevalidate())
295 allowedStale = value.value();
296#endif
297 bool hasNonZeroLifetime = !response.cacheControlContainsNoCache() && (WebCore::computeFreshnessLifetimeForHTTPFamily(response, now) > 0_ms || allowedStale > 0_ms);
298 bool possiblyReusable = response.hasCacheValidatorFields() || hasNonZeroLifetime;
299 if (!possiblyReusable)
300 return StoreDecision::NoDueToUnlikelyToReuse;
301 }
302
303 // Media loaded via XHR is likely being used for MSE streaming (YouTube and Netflix for example).
304 // Streaming media fills the cache quickly and is unlikely to be reused.
305 // FIXME: We should introduce a separate media cache partition that doesn't affect other resources.
306 // FIXME: We should also make sure make the MSE paths are copy-free so we can use mapped buffers from disk effectively.
307 auto requester = originalRequest.requester();
308 bool isDefinitelyStreamingMedia = requester == WebCore::ResourceRequest::Requester::Media;
309 bool isLikelyStreamingMedia = requester == WebCore::ResourceRequest::Requester::XHR && isMediaMIMEType(response.mimeType());
310 if (isLikelyStreamingMedia || isDefinitelyStreamingMedia)
311 return StoreDecision::NoDueToStreamingMedia;
312
313 return StoreDecision::Yes;
314}
315
316#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_SPECULATIVE_REVALIDATION)
317static bool inline canRequestUseSpeculativeRevalidation(const WebCore::ResourceRequest& request)
318{
319 if (request.isConditional())
320 return false;
321
322 if (request.requester() == WebCore::ResourceRequest::Requester::XHR || request.requester() == WebCore::ResourceRequest::Requester::Fetch)
323 return false;
324
325 switch (request.cachePolicy()) {
326 case WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReturnCacheDataElseLoad:
327 case WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReturnCacheDataDontLoad:
328 case WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::ReloadIgnoringCacheData:
329 return false;
330 case WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::UseProtocolCachePolicy:
331 case WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::RefreshAnyCacheData:
332 return true;
333 case WebCore::ResourceRequestCachePolicy::DoNotUseAnyCache:
334 ASSERT_NOT_REACHED();
335 return false;
336 }
337 return false;
338}
339#endif

341#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_STALE_WHILE_REVALIDATE)
342void Cache::startAsyncRevalidationIfNeeded(const WebCore::ResourceRequest& request, const NetworkCache::Key& key, std::unique_ptr<Entry>&& entry, const GlobalFrameID& frameID, std::optional<NavigatingToAppBoundDomain> isNavigatingToAppBoundDomain)
343{
344 m_pendingAsyncRevalidations.ensure(key, [&] {
345 auto addResult = m_pendingAsyncRevalidationByPage.ensure(frameID, [] {
346 return WeakHashSet<AsyncRevalidation>();
347 });
348 auto revalidation = makeUnique<AsyncRevalidation>(*this, frameID, request, WTFMove(entry), isNavigatingToAppBoundDomain, [this, key](auto result) {
349 ASSERT(m_pendingAsyncRevalidations.contains(key));
350 m_pendingAsyncRevalidations.remove(key);
351 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) Async revalidation completed for '%s' with result %d", key.identifier().utf8().data(), static_cast<int>(result));
352 });
353 addResult.iterator->value.add(*revalidation);
354 return revalidation;
355 });
356}
357#endif

359void Cache::browsingContextRemoved(WebPageProxyIdentifier webPageProxyID, WebCore::PageIdentifier webPageID, WebCore::FrameIdentifier webFrameID)
360{
361#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_STALE_WHILE_REVALIDATE)
362 auto loaders = m_pendingAsyncRevalidationByPage.take({ webPageProxyID, webPageID, webFrameID });
363 for (auto& loader : loaders)
364 loader.cancel();
365#endif
366}
367
368void Cache::retrieve(const WebCore::ResourceRequest& request, const GlobalFrameID& frameID, std::optional<NavigatingToAppBoundDomain> isNavigatingToAppBoundDomain, RetrieveCompletionHandler&& completionHandler)
369{
370 ASSERT(request.url().protocolIsInHTTPFamily());
371
372 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) retrieving %s priority %d", request.url().string().ascii().data(), static_cast<int>(request.priority()));
373
374 Key storageKey = makeCacheKey(request);
375 auto priority = static_cast<unsigned>(request.priority());
376
377 RetrieveInfo info;
378 info.startTime = MonotonicTime::now();
379 info.priority = priority;
380
381#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_SPECULATIVE_REVALIDATION)
382 bool canUseSpeculativeRevalidation = m_speculativeLoadManager && canRequestUseSpeculativeRevalidation(request);
383 if (canUseSpeculativeRevalidation)
384 m_speculativeLoadManager->registerLoad(frameID, request, storageKey, isNavigatingToAppBoundDomain);
385#endif
386
387 auto retrieveDecision = makeRetrieveDecision(request);
388 if (retrieveDecision != RetrieveDecision::Yes) {
389 completeRetrieve(WTFMove(completionHandler), nullptr, info);
390 return;
391 }
392
393#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_SPECULATIVE_REVALIDATION)
394 if (canUseSpeculativeRevalidation && m_speculativeLoadManager->canRetrieve(storageKey, request, frameID)) {
395 m_speculativeLoadManager->retrieve(storageKey, [networkProcess = makeRef(networkProcess()), request, completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler), info = WTFMove(info), sessionID = m_sessionID](std::unique_ptr<Entry> entry) mutable {
396 info.wasSpeculativeLoad = true;
397 if (entry && WebCore::verifyVaryingRequestHeaders(networkProcess->storageSession(sessionID), entry->varyingRequestHeaders(), request))
398 completeRetrieve(WTFMove(completionHandler), WTFMove(entry), info);
399 else
400 completeRetrieve(WTFMove(completionHandler), nullptr, info);
401 });
402 return;
403 }
404#endif
405
406 m_storage->retrieve(storageKey, priority, [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), request, completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler), info = WTFMove(info), storageKey, networkProcess = makeRef(networkProcess()), sessionID = m_sessionID, frameID, isNavigatingToAppBoundDomain](auto record, auto timings) mutable {
407 info.storageTimings = timings;
408
409 if (!record) {
410 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) not found in storage");
411 completeRetrieve(WTFMove(completionHandler), nullptr, info);
412 return false;
413 }
414
415 ASSERT(record->key == storageKey);
416
417 auto entry = Entry::decodeStorageRecord(*record);
418
419 auto useDecision = entry ? makeUseDecision(networkProcess, sessionID, *entry, request) : UseDecision::NoDueToDecodeFailure;
420 switch (useDecision) {
421 case UseDecision::AsyncRevalidate: {
422#if ENABLE(NETWORK_CACHE_STALE_WHILE_REVALIDATE)
423 auto entryCopy = makeUnique<Entry>(*entry);
424 entryCopy->setNeedsValidation(true);
425 startAsyncRevalidationIfNeeded(request, storageKey, WTFMove(entryCopy), frameID, isNavigatingToAppBoundDomain);
426#else
427 UNUSED_PARAM(frameID);
428 UNUSED_PARAM(this);
429#endif
430 FALLTHROUGH;
431 }
432 case UseDecision::Use:
433 break;
434 case UseDecision::Validate:
435 entry->setNeedsValidation(true);
436 break;
437 default:
438 entry = nullptr;
439 };
440
441#if !LOG_DISABLED
442 auto elapsed = MonotonicTime::now() - info.startTime;
443 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) retrieve complete useDecision=%d priority=%d time=%" PRIi64 "ms", static_cast<int>(useDecision), static_cast<int>(request.priority()), elapsed.millisecondsAs<int64_t>());
444#endif
445 completeRetrieve(WTFMove(completionHandler), WTFMove(entry), info);
446
447 return useDecision != UseDecision::NoDueToDecodeFailure;
448 });
449}
450
451void Cache::completeRetrieve(RetrieveCompletionHandler&& handler, std::unique_ptr<Entry> entry, RetrieveInfo& info)
452{
453 info.completionTime = MonotonicTime::now();
454 handler(WTFMove(entry), info);
455}

467std::unique_ptr<Entry> Cache::store(const WebCore::ResourceRequest& request, const WebCore::ResourceResponse& response, RefPtr<WebCore::SharedBuffer>&& responseData, Function<void(MappedBody&)>&& completionHandler)
468{
469 ASSERT(responseData);
470
471 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) storing %s, partition %s", request.url().string().latin1().data(), makeCacheKey(request).partition().latin1().data());
472
473 StoreDecision storeDecision = makeStoreDecision(request, response, responseData ? responseData->size() : 0);
474 if (storeDecision != StoreDecision::Yes) {
475 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) didn't store, storeDecision=%d", static_cast<int>(storeDecision));
476 auto key = makeCacheKey(request);
477
478 auto isSuccessfulRevalidation = response.httpStatusCode() == 304;
479 if (!isSuccessfulRevalidation) {
480 // Make sure we don't keep a stale entry in the cache.
481 remove(key);
482 }
483
484 return nullptr;
485 }
486
487 auto cacheEntry = makeEntry(request, response, WTFMove(responseData));
488 auto record = cacheEntry->encodeAsStorageRecord();
489
490 m_storage->store(record, [protectedThis = makeRef(*this), completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)](const Data& bodyData) mutable {
491 MappedBody mappedBody;
492#if ENABLE(SHAREABLE_RESOURCE)
493 if (auto sharedMemory = bodyData.tryCreateSharedMemory()) {
494 mappedBody.shareableResource = ShareableResource::create(sharedMemory.releaseNonNull(), 0, bodyData.size());
495 if (!mappedBody.shareableResource) {
496 if (completionHandler)
497 completionHandler(mappedBody);
498 return;
499 }
500 mappedBody.shareableResource->createHandle(mappedBody.shareableResourceHandle);
501 }
502#endif
503 if (completionHandler)
504 completionHandler(mappedBody);
505 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) stored");
506 });
507
508 return cacheEntry;
509}
510
511std::unique_ptr<Entry> Cache::storeRedirect(const WebCore::ResourceRequest& request, const WebCore::ResourceResponse& response, const WebCore::ResourceRequest& redirectRequest, std::optional<Seconds> maxAgeCap)
512{
513 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) storing redirect %s -> %s", request.url().string().latin1().data(), redirectRequest.url().string().latin1().data());
514
515 StoreDecision storeDecision = makeStoreDecision(request, response, 0);
516 if (storeDecision != StoreDecision::Yes) {
517 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) didn't store redirect, storeDecision=%d", static_cast<int>(storeDecision));
518 return nullptr;
519 }
520
521 auto cacheEntry = makeRedirectEntry(request, response, redirectRequest);
522
523#if ENABLE(RESOURCE_LOAD_STATISTICS)
524 if (maxAgeCap) {
525 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) capping max age for redirect %s -> %s", request.url().string().latin1().data(), redirectRequest.url().string().latin1().data());
526 cacheEntry->capMaxAge(maxAgeCap.value());
527 }
528#else
529 UNUSED_PARAM(maxAgeCap);
530#endif
531
532 auto record = cacheEntry->encodeAsStorageRecord();
533
534 m_storage->store(record, nullptr);
535
536 return cacheEntry;
537}
538
539std::unique_ptr<Entry> Cache::update(const WebCore::ResourceRequest& originalRequest, const Entry& existingEntry, const WebCore::ResourceResponse& validatingResponse)
540{
541 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) updating %s", originalRequest.url().string().latin1().data());
542
543 WebCore::ResourceResponse response = existingEntry.response();
544 WebCore::updateResponseHeadersAfterRevalidation(response, validatingResponse);
545
546 auto updateEntry = makeUnique<Entry>(existingEntry.key(), response, existingEntry.buffer(), WebCore::collectVaryingRequestHeaders(networkProcess().storageSession(m_sessionID), originalRequest, response));
547 auto updateRecord = updateEntry->encodeAsStorageRecord();
548
549 m_storage->store(updateRecord, { });
550
551 return updateEntry;
552}

554void Cache::remove(const Key& key)
555{
556 m_storage->remove(key);
557}

559void Cache::remove(const WebCore::ResourceRequest& request)
560{
561 remove(makeCacheKey(request));
562}

564void Cache::remove(const Vector<Key>& keys, Function<void()>&& completionHandler)

566 m_storage->remove(keys, WTFMove(completionHandler));
567}
568
569void Cache::traverse(Function<void(const TraversalEntry*)>&& traverseHandler)
570{
571 // Protect against clients making excessive traversal requests.
572 const unsigned maximumTraverseCount = 3;
573 if (m_traverseCount >= maximumTraverseCount) {
574 WTFLogAlways("Maximum parallel cache traverse count exceeded. Ignoring traversal request.");
575
576 RunLoop::main().dispatch([traverseHandler = WTFMove(traverseHandler)] () mutable {
577 traverseHandler(nullptr);
578 });
579 return;
580 }
581
582 ++m_traverseCount;
583
584 m_storage->traverse(resourceType(), { }, [this, protectedThis = makeRef(*this), traverseHandler = WTFMove(traverseHandler)] (const Storage::Record* record, const Storage::RecordInfo& recordInfo) mutable {
585 if (!record) {
586 --m_traverseCount;
587 traverseHandler(nullptr);
588 return;
589 }
590
591 auto entry = Entry::decodeStorageRecord(*record);
592 if (!entry)
593 return;
594
595 TraversalEntry traversalEntry { *entry, recordInfo };
596 traverseHandler(&traversalEntry);
597 });
598}

600String Cache::dumpFilePath() const
601{
602 return pathByAppendingComponent(m_storage->versionPath(), "dump.json");
603}
604
605void Cache::dumpContentsToFile()
606{
607 auto fd = openFile(dumpFilePath(), FileOpenMode::Write);
608 if (!isHandleValid(fd))
609 return;
610 auto prologue = String("{\n\"entries\": [\n").utf8();
611 writeToFile(fd, prologue.data(), prologue.length());
612
613 struct Totals {
614 unsigned count { 0 };
615 double worth { 0 };
616 size_t bodySize { 0 };
617 };
618 Totals totals;
619 auto flags = { Storage::TraverseFlag::ComputeWorth, Storage::TraverseFlag::ShareCount };
620 size_t capacity = m_storage->capacity();
621 m_storage->traverse(resourceType(), flags, [fd, totals, capacity](const Storage::Record* record, const Storage::RecordInfo& info) mutable {
622 if (!record) {
623 CString writeData = makeString(
624 "{}\n"
625 "],\n"
626 "\"totals\": {\n"
627 "\"capacity\": ", capacity, ",\n"
628 "\"count\": ", totals.count, ",\n"
629 "\"bodySize\": ", totals.bodySize, ",\n"
630 "\"averageWorth\": ", totals.count ? totals.worth / totals.count : 0, "\n"
631 "}\n}\n"
632 ).utf8();
633 writeToFile(fd, writeData.data(), writeData.length());
634 closeFile(fd);
635 return;
636 }
637 auto entry = Entry::decodeStorageRecord(*record);
638 if (!entry)
639 return;
640 ++totals.count;
641 totals.worth += info.worth;
642 totals.bodySize += info.bodySize;
643
644 StringBuilder json;
645 entry->asJSON(json, info);
646 json.append(",\n");
647 auto writeData = json.toString().utf8();
648 writeToFile(fd, writeData.data(), writeData.length());
649 });
650}
651
652void Cache::deleteDumpFile()
653{
654 WorkQueue::create("com.apple.WebKit.Cache.delete")->dispatch([path = dumpFilePath().isolatedCopy()] {
655 deleteFile(path);
656 });
657}

659void Cache::clear(WallTime modifiedSince, Function<void()>&& completionHandler)
660{
661 LOG(NetworkCache, "(NetworkProcess) clearing cache");
662
663 String anyType;
664 m_storage->clear(anyType, modifiedSince, WTFMove(completionHandler));
665
666 deleteDumpFile();
667}

669void Cache::clear()
670{
671 clear(-WallTime::infinity(), nullptr);
672}

677}
678
679void Cache::retrieveData(const DataKey& dataKey, Function<void(const uint8_t*, size_t)> completionHandler)
680{
681 Key key { dataKey, m_storage->salt() };
682 m_storage->retrieve(key, 4, [completionHandler = WTFMove(completionHandler)] (auto record, auto) mutable {
683 if (!record || !record->body.size()) {
684 completionHandler(nullptr, 0);
685 return true;
686 }
687 completionHandler(record->body.data(), record->body.size());
688 return true;
689 });
690}
691
692void Cache::storeData(const DataKey& dataKey, const uint8_t* data, size_t size)
693{
694 Key key { dataKey, m_storage->salt() };
695 Storage::Record record { key, WallTime::now(), { }, Data { data, size }, { } };
696 m_storage->store(record, { });
697}
